  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_3' aria-label=\" Vanashakti versus Union of India pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('3','2025','2025_5_2618_2647','2025INSC718'); ><font size='4'> <strong>VANASHAKTI<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>UNION OF INDIA </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 5 S.C.R. 2618</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 718</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010008402025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : ABHAY S. OKA<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, UJJAL BHUYAN</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Whether the 2017 Notification issued by the Ministry of Environment, Forest and Climate Change (MoEFCC) in the context of the EIA Notification 2006 for grant of ex post facto environmental clearances (EC) is legal and valid; Whether the 2021 Office Memorandum (OM) issued by Procedure (SOP) for projects that have commenced without an EC is legal and valid. Headnotes&dagger; Environment (Protection) Act, 1986 &ndash; EIA Notification 2006 &ndash; MoEFCC&rsquo;s 2017 Notification established process for grant of ex post facto or retrospective Environmental Clearance<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 16-05-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> WRIT PETITION (CIVIL) No. 1394/2023</font>  <span style='color:#212F3D' > | Direction Issue :</span><font color='green'> Writ Petitions and Civil Appeals allowed.</font> <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('3','2025','2025_5_2618_2647','2025INSC718','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><div class='col-a